    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.9.0-dev-613+gef18c9f9b\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\nNo it does the opposite. It does not change the last line in the file.\r\nVIM - Vi IMproved 9.0 (2022 Jun 28, compiled Aug 23 2022 20:18:58)\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nUbuntu 22.10\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nxfce4\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nAppimage\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\nCreate an `.editorconfig` file with the contents\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n[*]\r\ninsert_final_newline = false\r\n```\r\n\r\nOpen a file and save it. I use `vim-gitgutter` that tells me that the last line has been changed when I open the file.\r\n\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1689020/210649972-2540e401-80d4-49f3-ae38-e34bf26d9067.png)\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1689020/210652985-3cf955eb-fa43-4bec-bc23-29e2870721d3.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nDo not change the last line of the file?\r\nIt did not change the last line in neovim 0.6\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nIt changes the last line of the file, in every file it opens.\r\n\r\nIn my last neovim version (0.6) this did not happen.\r\nThis also does not happen in vim.\r\n\r\nIf I remove the `.editorconfig` file, the files are not changed.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
