        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Regardless of the outcome of the spec, it should be possible/documented to somehow override this behaviour in `init.lua`.\r\nI was able to workaround it by always unsetting it:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"BufEnter\", {\r\n    callback = function(args)\r\n        vim.bo[args.buf].fixendofline = null\r\n    end,\r\n})\r\n```\r\nHowever, it would be much better if there was a simple option that allowed changing this behaviour.\r\n(Unfortunately, `fixendofline` does not appear to be this option, as setting it to `false`/setting `nofixendofline` will not get the expected behaviour - it has to be set to `null`. Additionally, it is not possible to globally set it, as editorconfig will always override it.)",
